{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Chōshō|ja|長承|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1132]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Taira Tadamori|ja|平忠盛|12=draft|12=draft}} was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace. * {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1704]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1863]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1538]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nabeshima Naoshige|ja|鍋島直茂|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and founder of the Saga Domain (died [[1618]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1828]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nishimura Shigeki|ja|西村茂樹|12=draft|12=draft}}, an enlightenment thinker (died [[1902]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1192]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 77th Emperor of Japan (born [[1127]]).
