* {{ill|Chōshō|ja|長承}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1132]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日}}) – {{ill|Taira Tadamori|ja|平忠盛}} was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace.
* {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1704]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日}}) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永}}.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1863]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日}}) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori.
* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日}}) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.

== Births ==
* [[Tenbun]] 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1538]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日}}) – {{ill|Nabeshima Naoshige|ja|鍋島直茂}}, a military commander and founder of the Saga Domain (died [[1618]]).
* {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1828]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日}}) – {{ill|Nishimura Shigeki|ja|西村茂樹}}, an enlightenment thinker (died [[1902]]).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1192]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河天皇}}, the 77th Emperor of Japan (born [[1127]]).


