'''March 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Chōshō|ja|長承|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1132]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Taira Tadamori|ja|平忠盛|qq=|12=draft}} was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace.
* {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1704]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|qq=|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1863]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori.
* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.

