{{Not to be confused with|March 13|qq=March 13}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十三|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 13일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Chōshō|Chōshō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1132]] [[:en:April 7|April 7]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tadamori|Taira Tadamori]] was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace. * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1704]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]]. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:April 18|April 18]]) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=}} ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1538]] [[:en:April 12|April 12]]) – [[:en:Nabeshima Naoshige|Nabeshima Naoshige]], a military commander and founder of the Saga Domain (died [[1618]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1828]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Nishimura Shigeki|Nishimura Shigeki]], an enlightenment thinker (died [[1902]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1192]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Shirakawa|Emperor Go-Shirakawa]], the 77th Emperor of Japan (born [[1127]]).
