== Events == * [[:en:Chōshō|Chōshō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1132|1132]] [[:en:April 7|April 7]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tadamori|Taira Tadamori]] was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace. * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1704|1704]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]]. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1863|1863]] [[:en:April 18|April 18]]) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年}}[[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]] ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1538|1538]] [[:en:April 12|April 12]]) – [[:en:Nabeshima Naoshige|Nabeshima Naoshige]], a military commander and founder of the Saga Domain (died [[:en:1618|1618]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1828|1828]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Nishimura Shigeki|Nishimura Shigeki]], an enlightenment thinker (died [[1902]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1192|1192]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Shirakawa|Emperor Go-Shirakawa]], the 77th Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1127|1127]]).
