'''March 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|qid=Q96759842|1=senpu}}{{efn|ja|先負|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Chōshō|en|Chōshō|qid=Q1194264|lt=Chōshō|1=Chōshō}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1132|en|1132|qid=Q19582|lt=1132|1=1132}} {{ill|April 7|en|April 7|qid=Q2505|lt=April 7|1=April 7}}) – {{ill|Taira no Tadamori|en|Taira no Tadamori|qid=Q3083805|lt=Taira Tadamori|1=Taira no Tadamori}} was, for the first time as a samurai, granted permission to ascend to the imperial palace.
* {{ill|Hōei|en|Hōei|qid=Q1145262|lt=Hōei|1=Hōei}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1704|en|1704|qid=Q6824|lt=1704|1=1704}} {{ill|April 16|en|April 16|qid=Q2519|lt=April 16|1=April 16}}) – Following the Genroku great earthquake in November of the previous year, the era name was changed from Genroku to {{ill|Hōei|en|Hōei|qid=Q1145262|lt=Hōei|1=Hōei}}.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|en|Bunkyū|qid=Q730266|lt=Bunkyū|1=Bunkyū}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1863|en|1863|qid=Q7701|lt=1863|1=1863}} {{ill|April 18|en|April 18|qid=Q2521|lt=April 18|1=April 18}}) – Among the rōnin, 24 members who remained in Kyoto as part of the 【Rōshigumi】 were taken into service under the Kyoto Shugo and under Matsudaira Katamori.
* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|1=1868|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q7717}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|April 5|en|April 5|qid=Q2507|lt=April 5|1=April 5}}) – Saigō Takamori and Katsu Kaishū held a meeting in Edo; the following day, the peaceful surrender of Edo Castle was decided.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenbun|en|Tenbun|qid=Q1192853|lt=Tenbun|1=Tenbun}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1538|en|1538|qid=Q6470|lt=1538|1=1538}} {{ill|April 12|en|April 12|qid=Q2499|lt=April 12|1=April 12}}) – {{ill|Nabeshima Naoshige|en|Nabeshima Naoshige|qid=Q1039095|lt=Nabeshima Naoshige|1=Nabeshima Naoshige}}, a military commander and founder of the Saga Domain (died {{ill|1618|en|1618|qid=Q6801|lt=1618|1=1618}}).
* {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1828|en|1828|qid=Q7570|lt=1828|1=1828}} {{ill|April 26|en|April 26|qid=Q2532|lt=April 26|1=April 26}}) – {{ill|Nishimura Shigeki|en|Nishimura Shigeki|qid=Q3022461|lt=Nishimura Shigeki|1=Nishimura Shigeki}}, an enlightenment thinker (died {{ill|1902|en|1902|qid=Q2043|lt=1902|1=1902}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kenkyū|en|Kenkyū|qid=Q1193933|lt=Kenkyū|1=Kenkyū}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1192|en|1192|qid=Q19739|lt=1192|1=1192}} {{ill|April 26|en|April 26|qid=Q2532|lt=April 26|1=April 26}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|en|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qid=Q317984|lt=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|1=Emperor Go-Shirakawa}}, the 77th Emperor of Japan (born {{ill|1127|en|1127|qid=Q23827|lt=1127|1=1127}}).

